  "prompt": "What are some less fictioned movie everyone must watch?",
  "response": "Here are some highly recommended movies based on true stories or real events that everyone should consider watching:\n\n1. **\"Schindler's List\" (1993)**\n   - Directed by Steven Spielberg, this film tells the story of Oskar Schindler, a German businessman who saved the lives of over 1,000 Jewish refugees during the Holocaust by employing them in his factories.\n\n2. **\"The King's Speech\" (2010)**\n   - This film, directed by Tom Hooper, follows the story of King George VI, who struggles with a stammer and seeks help from an unorthodox speech therapist to overcome it before his coronation.\n\n3. **\"The Pursuit of Happyness\" (2006)**\n   - Directed by Gabriele Muccino and starring Will Smith, this movie is based on the true story of Chris Gardner, a homeless salesman who rises from adversity to become a successful stockbroker.\n\n4. **\"Hidden Figures\" (2016)**\n   - Directed by Theodore Melfi, this film celebrates the achievements of three African-American women who played crucial roles at NASA during the Space Race, despite facing racial and gender discrimination.\n\n5. **\"12 Years a Slave\" (2013)**\n   - Directed by Steve McQueen, this harrowing film recounts the true story of Solomon Northup, a free black man who was kidnapped and sold into slavery in the pre-Civil War United States.\n\n6. **\"Erin Brockovich\" (2000)**\n   - Directed by Steven Soderbergh, this film stars Julia Roberts as the titular character, a single mother who becomes a legal assistant and helps win a major lawsuit against a corporation responsible for polluting a town's water supply.\n\n7. **\"The Imitation Game\" (2014)**\n   - Directed by Morten Tyldum, this movie tells the story of Alan Turing, a mathematician who played a key role in breaking Nazi codes during World War II, and later faced persecution for his homosexuality.\n\n8. **\"Hotel Rwanda\" (2004)**\n   - Directed by Terry George, this film portrays the true story of Paul Rusesabagina, a hotel manager who sheltered over a thousand Tutsi refugees during the Rwandan genocide.\n\n9. **\"The Theory of Everything\" (2014)**\n   - Directed by James Marsh, this biographical drama focuses on the life of physicist Stephen Hawking, his groundbreaking work, and his relationship with his wife Jane.\n\n10. **\"Spotlight\" (2015)**\n    - Directed by Tom McCarthy, this film follows the Boston Globe's \"Spotlight\" team, which uncovered the massive scandal of child molestation and cover-up within the local Catholic Archdiocese.\n\nThese films are not only compelling and well-made but also provide valuable insights into real-life events and human experiences.",
